The paper deals with the mathematical framework to quantify the spatial correlation of interference in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the different point processes used to model the spatial distribution of devices, which is a topic related to stochastic processes (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper mentions Rayleigh fading, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
